---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Article from "../../components/Article.astro";
---

<Layout title="wanderer">
  <Article
    title="wanderer"
    section="self"
    updated="archive draft"
  >
    <p>
      the wanderer is the one who continues moving when certainty is no longer
      available. it is not defined by destination, but by the act of seeking
      itself.
    </p>

    <p>
      after paradox dissolves fixed answers, the wanderer emerges. direction
      remains, but it is no longer guaranteed.
    </p>

    <p>
      this movement can feel like exile, distance, or freedom, depending on how
      it is held.
    </p>

    <h2>seeking</h2>

    <p>
      the wanderer seeks, but not always with a clear goal. the search itself
      becomes the structure.
    </p>

    <p>
      this allows for discovery, but removes the comfort of certainty.
    </p>

    <h2>distance</h2>

    <p>
      there is often a sense of separation—from fixed identity, from stable
      meaning, from settled roles.
    </p>

    <p>
      this distance can feel like loss, but it also creates space for something
      new to appear.
    </p>

    <h2>return</h2>

    <p>
      the wanderer does not remain separate forever. movement eventually circles
      back, returning to identity—but changed by what has been encountered.
    </p>

    <p>
      this return closes the loop and begins it again.
    </p>

    <div class="mini-links">
      <a class="link-blue" href="/self">back to self index</a>
      <a class="link-blue" href="/self/identity">return to: identity</a>
      <a class="link-red" href="/self/paradox">paradox</a>
    </div>
  </Article>
</Layout>
